Borno State Governor Babagana Zulum yesterday made his first appointments. Those appointed are Alhaji Usman Jidda Shuwa, Secretary to the State Government (SSG); Dr. Babagana Wakil, Chief of Staff; and Dr. Mairo Mandara, Special Adviser and Coordinator, Sustainable Development, Partnership and Humanitarian Support. Others are Malam Isa Gusau Special Adviser, Public Relations and Strategy; Alhaji Baba Sheikh Haruna, Senior Special Assistant on Media, while Tanimu Adamu Tahir and AbdulRahman Ahmed Bundi, Special Assistants on Media and New Media respectively. Also appointed is Alhaji Ahmed Sanda, Senior Special Assistant on Protocol. Barr. Mustapha Ali Busuguma, Principal Private Secretary to the governor, in a statement, said all the appointments were with immediate effect. Bauchi Governor appoints new SSG, others Ahmed reappoints Gold as SSG, media aides Governor Mohammed swears in SSG, Chief of Staff, others Dear Esteemed reader, As part of our drive to keep improving the content of our newspaper, we are conducting a readership survey to enable us serve you better. Kindly take two minutes of your time to fill in this questionnaire. Thank you for your time. Click here to begin